# Separating categorical and continuous variables from the dataset
cate_val = []  # Initializing an empty list to store categorical variables
cont_val = []  # Initializing an empty list to store continuous variables
# Iterating through each column in the dataset
for column in data.columns:
    # Checking if the number of unique values in the column is less than or equal to 10
    if data[column].nunique()<=10:
        cate_val.append(column)
    else:
        cont_val.append(column)

import tkinter as tk
import joblib

# Function to get user input and make prediction
def show_entry_fields():
    # Get values from entry fields
    p1 = int(el.get())
    p2 = int(e2.get())
    p3 = int(e3.get())
    p4 = int(e4.get())
    p5 = int(e5.get())
    p6 = int(e6.get())
    p7 = int(e7.get())
    p8 = int(e8.get())
    p9 = int(e9.get())
    p10 = float(e10.get())
    p11 = int(e11.get())
    p12 = int(e12.get())
    p13 = int(e13.get())

    # Load pre-trained model
    model = joblib.load('model_joblib_heart')

    # Make prediction using the model
    result = model.predict([[p1, p2, p3, p4, p5, p6, p7, p8, p8, p10, p11, p12, p13]])

    # Display prediction outcome
    if result == 0:
        label_result = Label(master, text="No Heart Diseases").grid(row=31)
    else:
        label_result = Label(master, text="Possibility of Heart Diseases").grid(row=31)

# Create the main window

master.title("Heart Diseases Prediction System")
